# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# HOW TO SET UP YOUR .env FILE (do this once before running any scripts)
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
#
# 1. Copy this file:
#       cp .env.example .env
#
# 2. Edit .env and replace the placeholder below with YOUR name and ASU email.
#
# WHY: The SEC EDGAR API requires every automated caller to identify themselves.
#      This is NOT an API key — it is literally just your name and email.
#      No sign-up, no account, no registration needed.
#
# FORMAT: "First Last email@asu.edu"   (name, space, email — keep the quotes)
#
# EXAMPLES (use your own info, not these):
#   SEC_USER_AGENT="Taljinder Singh taljinder@asu.edu"
#   SEC_USER_AGENT="Raj Kumar Mahto raj.mahto@asu.edu"
#   SEC_USER_AGENT="Arnab Mitra arnab.mitra@asu.edu"
#   SEC_USER_AGENT="Jacob Kuriakose jacob.kuriakose@asu.edu"
#   SEC_USER_AGENT="Aditya Pokharna aditya.pokharna@asu.edu"
#
# NOTE: The .env file is gitignored and will NEVER be committed to GitHub.
#       Each teammate creates their own .env locally.
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

SEC_USER_AGENT="Your Name your_email@asu.edu"

# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# GROQ API KEY (required for strict LLM-only runtime)
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Free sign-up: https://console.groq.com (no credit card needed)
# After sign-up, go to API Keys section and create a key.
# This key is required for planner, policy/reflexion synthesis, and final narrative.
#
GROQ_API_KEY="your_groq_api_key_here"
